{%- from "plugins/css/component.njk" import component with context -%}

<article class="[][ showcase ][ page-sections ]">
	<header class="[ stack-lg ][ text-center theme-black ][ page-section book-cover ]">
		<div class="[ stack ][][]">
			<p class="[][][ book-cover-subtitle ]">
				{{ site.subtitle }}
			</p>

			<h1 class="[][][ book-cover-title ]">
				{{ site.title }}
			</h1>

			<p class="[ center ][ measure ][]">
				Launch <a href="https://www.overdrive.com/apps/libby/">Libby</a> from any web page to see if a book is available to borrow from your local library.
			</p>
		</div>

		<a
			class="[][][ cta ]"
			href="/install"
		>Install Now</a>
	</header>

	<main>
		<section class="[][ text-center theme-cream-light ][ page-section ]">
			<div class="[ center stack ][ measure ][]">
				<h2 class="[][][ page-section-heading ]">Libby is awesome</h2>
				<p>An app for Android, iOS, and the web, Libby is a great way to borrow e-books, audiobooks, and more from your public library—for free.</p>

				{% call component( "Disclaimer", {} ) %}
					<p>Check This Out is not affiliated with or endorsed by OverDrive, the makers of Libby. <a href="/about">Learn more</a></p>
				{% endcall %}

				<p>But you’re not always using Libby when a new title or author catches your eye.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="[][ text-center theme-yellow ][ page-section ]">
			<div class="[ center stack ][ measure ][]">
				<h2 class="[][][ page-section-heading ]">New books abound</h2>
				<p>There are so many places online to find something new to read — best-of lists, links from the group chat, virtual book clubs, and on and on.</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="[][][ page-section theme-cream ]">
			<div class="[ center stack-lg ][ measure ][]">
				<div class="[ stack ][][]">
					<h2 class="[][][ page-section-heading ]">Start a new book with just a few taps</h2>
					<p>No matter where you are on the internet, {{ site.title }} makes it a cinch to borrow or reserve a new book in Libby.</p>
					<p>Select the title or author, choose {{ site.title }}, and jump straight to a search in Libby.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="[ stack ][][]">
					<h2 class="[][][ page-section-subheading ]">Available everywhere</h2>
					<p>Best of all, {{ site.title }} is a special kind of link you add next to all your other bookmarks. That means in any browser, on any platform, you’re always just a few clicks or taps away from your next book.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</article>
